Preheat your oven to 200°C. Pop the @Mayonnaise{1} in a #mixing bowl{} along with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} and add the @Cauliflower Florets{300%g}. Use your hands to coat the florets lightly in the mayo. In another mixing bowl, combine the @Panko Breadcrumbs{30%g} and @Caribbean Style Jerk{1}. Lightly oil a #baking tray{}.

Working in batches, drop a few cauliflower florets into the breadcrumbs and toss to coat. Transfer to your baking tray and repeat with the remaining florets. Roast the jerk cauliflower nuggets on the top shelf of your oven until golden and crispy on the outside and soft inside, ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces) into small pieces. Peel and grate the @Ginger{1}(peeled and grated). Halve the @Bell Pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded) and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Pick the @Rosemary{1/2}(leaves picked from stalks, stalks discarded). Halve the @Red Chilli{1/2}(halved lengthways, deseeded and finely chopped) lengthways, deseed and finely chop. Drain and rinse the @Black Beans{1}(drained and rinsed) in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. When hot, add the onion and cook, stirring, until soft, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the ginger, pepper, @Smoked Paprika{1}, rosemary and a pinch of chilli and cook, stirring, for another ~{2%minutes}. Stir in the @Finely Chopped Tomatoes{1} and black beans. Bring to the boil, reduce the heat then simmer until thick and tomatoey, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @Coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Stir the @Baby Spinach{125%g} a handful at a time into the stew to wilt it.

Stir half the coriander through the stew then divide between your bowls. Top with the jerk cauli nuggets and finish with a sprinkling of the remaining coriander. Enjoy!